cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

The paper proposes a method for brain lesion segmentation using convolutional neural networks and semi-supervised learning. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. The use of unannotated data and the adaptation of the mean teacher model also suggest relevance to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the application of the method to medical imaging indicates potential relevance to multimedia (cs.MM).
